'''Sparkle-bop''' was a genre of [[Music/Legends|music]] that involved catchy or hummable melodies, simplistic three-chord structures, repetitive riffs or "hooks", and lightweight lyrics, that were deceptively simple at best. Sparkle-bop became popular during the time of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].

